RBC 14 Environment-2. All the equipment must operate in the ambient environment temperature range:
a) - 40°C to +70°C for outdoor equipment;
b) -10°C to +50°C for indoor equipment. The use of air conditioning systems is accepted, according to the applicable standards, for the cases when the offered equipment does not meet the specified limits. Any air conditioning is considered in this case to be for safety and work with the same reserve as the equipment on which it is used. The air conditioning must operate when the UPS is supplied from the main source or from the generator group. (LC)

RBC 15 Measures must be taken to protect the outdoor equipment against: (LC)
- theft, vandalism and sabotage;
- vibrations;
- water ingress;
- dust ingress.
For this, containers, cabinets, pickets and boxes for outdoor equipment must be fitted with:
- an adequate protection system against moisture;
- an effective locking system;
- doors with contacts for containers and cabinets that signal the central post when they are opened.
Water-sensitive equipment must be placed 1 meter above ground level.

RBC 253 Data preparation (as a specific application) consists of at least creating the fixed track configuration data including: (LC)
-	infrastructure profile data;
-	route conditions and dependencies.

RBC 302 It must be possible to integrate various types of information (such as diagrams and texts) in a single physical screen, including(LC):
-	Overviews;
-	Alarm list.
